            <p class="author-name">Professional Athlete</p>
            <p class="author-title">Clayfield, Brisbane</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section section alt-bg">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Clayfield Property Buying FAQs</h2>
        <div class="faq-grid">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Why is Clayfield considered a blue-chip Brisbane suburb?</h3>
            <p>Clayfield offers premium inner-city location, top-tier schools, heritage character homes, excellent transport, and limited land supply. It's consistently ranked among Brisbane's most desirable and resilient property markets with strong capital growth history.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What property types are available in Clayfield?</h3>
            <p>Clayfield is renowned for classic Queenslander homes, character workers' cottages, and modern architect-designed properties. The suburb also features quality apartments near the train station and some contemporary townhouses.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How competitive is buying property in Clayfield?</h3>
            <p>Extremely competitive due to limited supply and high demand from affluent buyers and families seeking top schools. Quality properties often attract multiple offers. Professional representation and off-market access provide significant advantages.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Is Clayfield suitable for professional athletes and executives?</h3>
            <p>Yes, Clayfield is ideal for high-performing professionals. Close proximity to CBD and airport, excellent sporting facilities, prestigious addresses, privacy, and capital growth potential make it perfect for athletes and executives.</p>
          </div>

